\frac{\sin(2xy)}{x^2+y^2} = \frac{\sin(2xy)}{2xy} \cdot \frac{2xy}{x^2+y^2}.
\frac{2xy}{x^2+y^2} = \frac{2 \rho^2 \cos\vartheta \sin\vartheta}{\rho^2} = \sin 2\vartheta.
